title: Boys Cross Country Roundup: Marion Harding Invitational
text:
Boys Cross Country Roundup: Marion Harding Invitational Telegraph-Forum staff report 11:18 p.m. EDT October 10, 2015 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Harding Invitational 
Bucyrus was tenth (300 points), led by Carson Pirnstill (36th, 17:42), Dakota Hedrick (50th, 18:11), Noah Johnson (61st, 18:34), Tyler Rittenhour (72nd, 19:07) and Mason Kent (81st, 20:00). 
Ashland was first at the Harding Invitational (46 points) out of 13 teams on Saturday. 
Fostoria Booster Invitational 
Mohawk placed thirteenth (2317 points), led by Owen Lacey (27th, 18:17), Jared Vargo (39th, 18:42), Lyndon Helton (75th, 19:53), Ryan Lacey (81st, 20:15) and Wyatt Price (95th, 21:43). 
Liberty Center placed first (49 points) out of 12 teams on Saturday. Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1RAuuCa TOP VIDEOS
